# Conflict policy for high-churn docs so concurrent branches never block a merge
# (and the auto-push into main keeps flowing). See scripts/setup-git.sh / AGENTS.md.
#
# CHANGELOG is append-only (newest entry on top). Use the built-in union merge
# driver so concurrent branch entries auto-combine (keep BOTH sides) instead of
# producing merge conflicts. union is also honored by GitHub's server-side merge.
CHANGELOG.txt merge=union
#
# README conflicts auto-resolve by accepting the INCOMING (theirs) version. This
# uses the custom `theirs` driver configured by scripts/setup-git.sh, so it
# applies to local/agent merges (run that script once per clone). GitHub's
# server-side merge does not execute custom drivers, so for PR auto-merge README
# conflicts still need a local merge with the driver configured.
README.md merge=theirs
